Components copied verbatim from AGT (MIT headers retained)
---------------------------------------------------------
  plugin/src/poisoning.mjs   <- AGT text/poisoning helpers

Components adapted from AGT (MIT headers retained)
-------------------------------------------------
  plugin/src/policy.mjs  <- AGT governance engine
    Adapted for OpenCode's in-process, single-shell-tool model:
    - retargeted to OpenCode tool names (lowercase read/bash/etc.);
    - recordAudit() rewritten to persist a cross-session SHA-256 hash chain,
      and getPolicyStatus()/formatPolicySummary() rewritten to read and verify
      that on-disk chain (the upstream in-memory AuditLogger neither loads prior
      entries nor exposes a load API, so it cannot chain across sessions);
    - the audit chain is keyless and tamper-evident, not tamper-proof
      (see README "Known limitations").
  plugin/src/sdk-loader.mjs  <- AGT SDK loader, reworked as a bundle-friendly
    shim so esbuild can inline the SDK into a single artifact.

  config/default-policy.json and config/profiles/*.json are derived from the
  AGT Copilot CLI policy profiles, retargeted to OpenCode tool names, with the
  shell command rules expanded to cover PowerShell, find/xargs, and encoded
  bypasses (so dangerous commands routed through OpenCode's single `bash` tool
  are caught regardless of shell). The shipped default is the `balanced` tier.

Vendored / bundled SDK
----------------------
  build.mjs bundles @microsoft/agent-governance-sdk (AGT TypeScript SDK, MIT),
  the adapter, and the AGT engine into the single artifact
  assets/agt-governance.js. The AGT SDK is "Public Preview".

